item.description:
@RUNE-PK wrote:

[quote=“zuppers, post:19, topic:548235”][quote author=RUNE-PK link=topic=667139.msg4462370#msg4462370 date=1418190400]

[quote author=zuppers link=topic=667139.msg4461489#msg4461489 date=1417748221]

Well you’re closer to min than max, but I still feel like those are a still a little too high
[/quote]Those are just the min/max recorded temperatures from that session.

@op what is that model number for the processor after TL-?

Its tl-64
[/quote]Your processoror has been rated with a maximum operational temperature of 95c, now obviously that doesn’t mean you should be operating it that hot but it does mean your temps are fine.[/quote]

My brother went to school for computers or whatever lol and he said it was a burnt header, he also said as long as i keep it cool it wont do anymore damage and it hasn’t so far so I have a cooling box for that and it goes really slow when its hot it locks up and i have to force restart it, But its always cool now

[quote=“Ashi, post:15, topic:548235”][quote author=Frell link=topic=667139.msg4461564#msg4461564 date=1417800024]
Careful not to get too close to the min limit, that hardware component may shut off from being too cool (warm is most optimal for sending information). If you do hit the limit a lot i’d suggest putting your computer near a window in the sunlight or under a heated blanket.
[/quote]
Never heard of that happening. A cool computer is always good.[/quote]
The ability to detect sarcasm is strong with you.
